00123 #ifndef CI_BASIC_RESULTS_DEFINED
00124 #define CI_BASIC_RESULTS_DEFINED
00125 // These result follow HRESULT model, where success result>=0, error result<0, for Cidana specified error code, please refer to CIPL_ERROR
00126 enum
00127 {       // CI_RESULT return types
00128         CI_SOK                                  = 0x00000000,
00129         CI_SFALSE                               = 0x00000001,
00130         CI_EPENDING                             = 0x8000000A,
00131         CI_ENOTIMPL                             = 0x80004001,
00132         CI_ENOINTERFACE                 = 0x80004002,
00133         CI_EPOINTER                             = 0x80004003,
00134         CI_EABORT                               = 0x80004004,
00135         CI_EFAIL                                = 0x80004005,
00136         CI_EHANDLE                              = 0x80004006,
00137         CI_EUNEXPECTED                  = 0x8000ffff,   // returned if decoder not initialized yet
00138         CI_EACCESSDENIED                = 0x80070005,
00139         CI_EOUTOFMEMORY                 = 0x8007000E,
00140         CI_EINVALIDARG                  = 0x80070057,
00141         CI_EPROPSETUNSUPPORTED  = 0x80070492,
00142         CI_EPROPIDUNSUPPORTED   = 0x80070490,
00143         CI_ELICENSE                             = 0x80040FFF,
00144         CI_EINPBUFTOOSMALL              = 0x80041200,
00145         CI_EOUTBUFTOOSMALL              = 0x80041201,
00146         CI_EMODENOTSUPPORTED    = 0x80041202,
00147         CI_EBITSTREAM                   = 0x80041203,
00148 // module specific codes ¨C should start from 0x80040200 and will overlap between modules. 
00149 // CI_MODULENAME_E(type) ==>  [0x80040200, 0x8004ffff]  (HRESULT  facility  ITF,  code range 0x0200-0xffff) 
00150 // CI_MODULENAME_S(type) ==>  [0x00000200, 0x0000ffff]
00151 };
